<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[72296]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA['Coming back from the Font del Gat']]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Exhibition.</strong> An exhibition remembers Montjuïc's popular drinking fountains, places that attracted many Barcelona residents at the end of the 19th century.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The <i>Baixant de la Font del Gat. Les fonts populars de Montjuïc </i> [Coming back from the Font del Gat. The popular Montjuïc drinking fountains] takes a look at the lives of city residents at the end of the 19th and the beginning of the 20th centuries, through the drinking fountains found around Montjuïc mountain. The exhibition contains photographs, illustrations and lithographs, as well as texts and sound effects that take visitors back to the past.</p>
<p>The drinking fountains were very popular places and for many Barcelona residents they were a major part of their leisure activities and celebrations. The most popular drinking fountains are: the Font del Gat, the Font Trobada, the Font dels Tres Pins, the Font del Geperut, the Font del Tir, the Font del Parc de Baix or Font de Laribal, the Font d’en Conna, the Font de la Vista Alegre, the Font de la Guatlla, the Font d’en Pessetes, the Font de la Mina and the Font de la Satalia.</p>
